values:
Well here I am just over half way through my 1st term at the University of Sussex!! I have had a pretty amazing time of it really! I love my course, I love my housemates, and I love nights out in Brighton!! Will has been to see me twice which is excellent!! Cos I miss him soo much!!

As for nights out here, they Rock, like actually! only had a couple of not so good nights out when we strayed to honey club, and Casablanca on student night (too busy for Bonnie!!) However a couple of decent rock clubs, and many cool rock nights keep me happy! 

As for friends, I have developed quite a tight group of friends in my house, then there is everyone else in my house, who I get on with really well. 1 good friend on my course, and a few people I get on with quite well :) So it's all good!! I was so afraid I wouldn't have anyone to relate to but I've been really lucky and found some quality people :)

As for work!! This is my downside!! damn uni, making me work!! Whats up with that!! I have been really stressed out recently cos I've had so much work to do. I'm getting on top of it now, so I'm fairly pleased. Although I'm not happy with the fact I have to do an oral presentation in a TV Studio!! Terrifying! All in all the course is great, but I swear I spend too much time locked in my room working! 

I miss all the guys from back home, and it will be really good to see everyone at christmas!! I'm looking forward to it kindof now, cos I haven't been home this term. We will see what I think when I'm there.

It's Wills birthday at the weekend!!! yay!!! So I get to go see him in Leeds!! means a mondo train journey, but I'm going down with Liz so it's all cool!! Quite worried about my Will as he's not happy with uni :( I just hope I can be some support to him!

Love to all!!
Bonnie
xx

Well I'm now in my first week of term here at Sussex Uni!!! Freshers week was pretty cool, everyone in my house is really cool, we've been quite lucky :D quite a range of people, and we all get on so far :) Freshers week was tiring, all of us spent the week being knackered! We did go out a lot, but it wasn't a drunken freshers week all the time! I had a lot of fun though :) been to most the bars on campus now, there are a lot of tiny ones tucked away, apparently one in the library, lol ?? Sussex uni is awesome and Brighton is such a cool place to live, been in a couple of times shopping and a couple of times out. For some reason both the nights out ended up at the same club, lol. Will definatley check out some other places, I really want to go to a place called the ocean rooms and funky buddha as they seem to have a couple of quality nights, ineveitably end up at the honey club at some point as thats the cool place to go although the name sounds a bit cringeworthy. I am avoiding creation at all costs as it is well know as a crappy club and a meatmarket! Found a quality rock night on guess what a Tuesday :) I had far too much to drink when we went, I spent the entire of wednesday in bed after going to the worst lecture due to being hungover. Probablt doesn't help that my house mate Alice has infected me with Freshers Flu :( Anyways i'm rambling cos theres so much to say but i don't knwo how to say it. I'm having the best time here and I love it, plus my course seems pretty cool and I have made a friend on my course which I wasn't sure if I would!! Plus I've joined the Kickboxing club so watch out at christmas or I'll kick ur ass :) he he 
the only thing about being at Uni is that I miss everyone, needless to say it's painful being apart from Will but we talk almost every day, so it will all work out :) I'll try and update this more now that I have the net in my room. 
Take care and have fun!

I'm sooo tired, I have been awake for about an hour! It seems all I'm doing recently is staying up really late, and getting up too early!! Lol, but its all good, I am certainly not complaining that I have stuff to do, just that I'm Kanackered. 
Last night was pretty crazy, Started at Fiona's with drinking games, which was quite funny even though I was obscenely late. Went to the Well, had a chat with a few people I haven't spoken to in a while, which was really good. Generally just chilled out. Then we went to Sugar, which was ok. As the weather has been so bloody hot and muggy I decided to wear as little as possible without looking like a slut, so a skirt was worn! An idea which was shared by Kat and Lucinda, which is quite odd as none of us wear skirts!! I felt rather over dressed in the Well, but was quite thankful in Sugar as it was very very hot!! After Sugar went back to Lauren's house, as that was where I was staying (notice the word staying and not sleeping!) had to lead Fiona back as she was so drunk she couldn't walk in a straight line :D Lauren's was cool, Lauren, Nicky, Matt H and Tom and I stayed up all night watching freeview!! Lol, it was cool though, did get some sleep in the morning when they were watching Spiderman. Films have the uncanny ability to make me sleepy, even if I am really interested in them. I have never seen the entire length of 'Seven'. Got back home at about 9:30 courtesy of my mum, and had a shower because I felt rather minging, then went to bed to get up at about 4. 
Monday I went straight from work to John's house, where many people were. It was cool, nice to just sit around and chat to people, we don't do it often enough. Was going to stay there but Will had to get up in the morning to make a phone call, so we went back to his instead. which seemed preferable as I could stay in bed! :) 
As for the week before that, I've seen Will a lot, which is nice, as we have become much closer now :D It's surprising how you can know someone so long, but not really know them very well. 
Tired now must stop typing and find something constuctive to do. I have this strange feeling of paranoia hanging over me, which is rather unsettling, would like to get rid of that pretty soon. Other than that life's cool!

x

I was supposed to go to Hatton Country farm with Fiona today, but I slept in! I do that too often, I have such problems getting up in the morning, I always have done, its quite annoying really. So instead I'm bumming around at home doing bugger all, might try and get some work done in a bit. I have this essay to do on a case study of a lad with Schizophrenia and it seems quite interesting, an essay I actually want to write for a change. 
Saturday was cool, after my shift at work my dad picked me up and we went guitar shopping! After travelling the whole of Warwickshire looking at different guitars, and trying a few out, we found ourselves back in Leamington in Regent Guitars deciding to get the one I saw on the website anyway. Not that all the looking was a waste of time, it gave me an idea of all the other guitars I could have, but I was right in the first place, I definitely want an Ibanez. So I'm now awaiting a call from the guy there, hopefully they will have found the model I want so I can have it soon :) It's quite scary spending so much money on something, but it's definitely worth it :D I can't wait to have it!!! 
Saturday night was cool too, although I AM on a non-drinking thing, I changed the rules a little Saturday night. Chris was begging me to get drunk with him as he rarely does, and then offered to give me some of his absinthe. After a lot of deliberation I took up his offer. It was a good night met up with Woolley, Kat, Lu and one of Lu's uni friends. Then later on saw Hayley and met up with Fiona. So it was all go, cool to have so many people around.
Hmmmm, I'm hungry now, I haven't eaten yet today, so I'm gonna go munch as I have little else to say. 

Take Care!!

Ok know I had a busy day ahead of me on Tuesday, and that was right, but I didn't realised such a busy week to follow. I haven't had the time or the energy to post whats been going on, even now I'm not going to have enough time to do it justice, so I'll leave the details till later. 
The funny thing is, is that I haven't really gotten anything done, I've just been going out, having fun, then recovering. My room is a state, which it hasn't been in such a while, and I haven't even started my assignment. Starting to worry that I;m not going to get this diploma done. Today is such a nice day I don't want to waste it in here, so I'll keep it short. Stay posted for stories of the week. 

Last night was relaxing but the only night of the week when I was bored and just wanted to go home, I don't want to feel that again. 

 - x -

Not much to say really, I'm feeling quite invigourated! Went to the gym this morning, after a much needed lie-in and then had a nice long shower :) 
I've had  few days of doing not much, now I have to get back on track. Last night was a chill out night, and I caught up on the episodes of Angel and Charmed I haven't watched yet. The two things on the TV I actually watch nowadays, well except for neighbours. So tonight its work for me, I have started the reading for my assignment but I need to get it finished tonight and do the prep work for the essays. I need to get work done so I'm not still doing this course when I start Uni, that would be a nightmare! So no I'm not going out, saving myself for tommorrow night with Oli and Joy, and whoever else may be involved. Despite people being back, having a life here i.e. working seems to be getting in the way of me seeing anyone. I'm not doing obertime next week, and probably not over the rest of the holidays, so i should be able to get into the swing of things. I found out my pay dates are changing so I'll be getting paid twice this month, which is really convenient as I want to get my guitar asap so I can start playing with it :) Plus next paycheck is a five week month so muchos mula! 
So feeling pretty good in general, heres to another good month!

Went out with Woolley on Tuesday, was a very cool time. It was really nice to catch up for a change, haven't seen him properly in a few months really. Went down the well, had a chat, then down to sugar for a boogie. Which was better than usual as I had someone to dance with. Woolley stayed at mine and we had a long talk into the night, just like before. 

Went out with Joy Saturday night, which was interesting, Joy and I had an interesting long chat about a variety of random stuff. The Well was dead, and Joy's boyfriends ex turned up so we went for a drive. Ended up in Stratford, not much of a clue where we were, but it was fun none the less. On the way home we ended up having to pull up in Warwick and going for a pee in the park. Which was amusing, especially when Joy saw there was a man in a window that she was in full view of. 

Been a quiet week really, but pretty good, got quite a bit done, essays, washing, music, etc. Suppose I managed to have two nights out with people I haven't really spoken to in a while, which is really good. 

Well, neighbours is finished now, back to essay writing :) well at least research. 

Get paid on Wednesday, none of this being poor malarkey, got lots to sort out though :)

 - x -

Last night kicked ass, Got very very drunk, but not as drunk as my companions, Nicky, Fiona and Lauren (in order of drunkenness). Well maybe I was worse than Lauren. We started the night off a Nicky's and drank some wine (2 bottles to be precise) then to Stresa for a quick cocktail, in the coolest glasses!! Then to the Well. We had a bit of a female empowerment thing going on, something which is foreign to me as most of my close friends are usually guys. But it was a nice change I much enjoyed it. Going out again tonight, but the weather is crap so I'm planning to drive :) so no drinkies. Looking forward to going up to John's, usually I would be terrified of all the people that I don't know, but I need some change right now. 

Sleepy sleepy!

 - x -

Not much to say really. It's well cold today and I have a headache :( so I'm not in the mood to say much.

Had a pretty cool weekend, Fiona's last weekend on detox so I'm looking forward to next weekend when we'll be out on one. 

Friday night was quite quiet, as I joined Fiona in not drinking, we had a nice chat though, and Fiona amused me with her pointing out the guys she thought were fit, and me giving my opinion. Fiona and I do have very different tastes though, I can see what she sees in these guys, but not for me really. Then again I don't usually look at guys like that, I'm not sure why, maybe all these years of either going out with someone or really liking one particular person. 

Saturday night was a good one, I did consider driving, but as John was coming out thought I would have a quiet drink. Oh no, not  queit drink, I got rather drunk. Fiona just sat there and laughed at me all night. Apparently I was quite entertaining. It was all good though. The end of the night did bring one bad emotion of a mix between jelousy and upset, but without going into detail I decided to ignore it and get on. Went for the all too often splif meeting around the corner, of which i didn't have any as usual, as I don't mix weed and alcohol, if I ever have weed at all. It was funny, as I tried to divert a crappy converation by saying "wow thats a big tree!" this turned into a debate of how tall the statue of liberty is, and after some estimation and arguing John and I finally decided it was about 7 of those trees tall, others didn't agree, but I don't think they could comprehend just how big the statue of liberty is. Got a taxi home, much against my normal behaviour, but I really couldnt be arsed to walk, and by myself, I wasn't in the mood. 

I've been considering my journal, and I have noticed I only update it when I go out, and not about other things, like my random thoughts or whatever, might include these in the future :)

Tuesday night was a good one, I really geuinely had a nice time, it wasn't crazy or anything, just a good night. Spoke to a good few people, facinated by Fiona's Detox diet, she's doing a full on detox, I really respect her in a way for that, I know I couldn't do it. 

I'm thinking about not drinking for a while, more than a week this time (thanks for taking the piss Oli :D) I think I rely on it too much sometimes to be able to socialise, People don't believe me but I am quite shy, and need that extra boost. Not drinking now, when everyone has gone back to uni, will be a true test of myself. I have become more confident, but I need to work on that. People scare me. 

Went to sugar, only the second time, wasn't as drunk as last time, but I think I enjoyed it more. There was a fair crowd of us, and I always enjoy a good boogie. 

Had a fairly entertaining walk home, Adam Payne and I trying to convince Ben that he wasn't a bad person, which was entertaining in a way because he was so drunk and blaming himself for things that really aren't his fault, but quite sad because there was most probably something in it. After waiting forever and a day for Ben and Adam to skin up, whilst Oli and Mark retrived some random stuff from behind the garage, we finally started our final part of the walk home. Oli and Chris buggered off because they didn't want to wait, fair enough, I would have gone with them, but as Mark was staying for Ben thought it might be good to have someone to walk home with that lives so close. After Ben left to go home had a nice chat with Mark which made the rest of the journey more pleasent. Got home and straight into bed. nice. 

Oli's last weekend this weekend, Got to be a good one

Happy New Year everyone!! :)

I wish I had posted new years day, but I ws with family and such so I didn't. I feel my journal entries lack feeling, because I don't write them at the time, but Oli told me that I have  good balance between description and feeling, so I'm fairly contented now.

New years eve! What a night! Needless to say I got very drunk, and danced a lot. I really enjoyed it, I can honestly say its the best new year I have had in my life, so many people where there, so many people I knew :) I hugged and kissed so many people, it was a great atmosphere, I was happy :) However I did crash at the end of the night, coming down from being drunk and then talking to Mark, compleatly fucking up everything I said to him, as usual. The walk home cheered me up though, despite the fact it was cold and rainy i was in good company and we had a laugh. However Adam, Chris and I ended up going down a kind of allyway and there's this strange building with a grated window, looking into that window freaked me out entirely, it was so dark in there, with a small amount of light, but I felt something was there, and the grate being bent played tricks with my eyes looking like there was movement inside, urgh! didnt like that. 

Friday night was one of merriment despite the lack of drinking on my part. I wasn;t going to go out initially, i finished work at 9 with a headacheso went home, turned on my phone got a text from Fiona asking me if I wanted to go out, decided I should and off down the well I went, and glad I did. There was a different crowd there, which was nice. Had a bit of a chat with Matt Crum which was cool, as I don't really know him, and we havent really spoken before, but he's a decent guy, it was nice to talk. spent the latter half of the evening with adam payne which was nice, had a game with him at deer hunting, had a chat, and with many other people. It's all good.

Last night was an unexpected event, but I'm so glad it happened. I was going out with Fiona for one of out usual nights, go out, drink, see some people, have a laugh. That did happen, however I got an added bonus. Oli and I started talking and didn't stop untill for in the morning. Except for some amusing interludes from a very drunk Rachel, Fiona, and scary Andy. I felt like I really connected with Oli last night in way that I haven't with him before, and I'm not even sure with anyone. We have some really similar thoughts and we have a certain understanding, it was nice, I really enjoyed it.

Monday Night was strange, going back to Binswood, seeing people I probably will never see, or at least speak to again. It all went well though, the only really boring part of the evening being Mr. Hazeldine rambling on about school statistics which couldnt have been much more boring. I don't see why he chose to give us a run down on that, seems to take away from the personal achievement, well at least to the extent of how he went on about it. 
Anyway, afterwards we all went down the pub, it wasnt as good as I would like it to have been, maybe at the weekend it will be better, we'll see. 

Last night I was strange, I didn't go to the Well! I didn't drink! It was good though, I went to Heathers house to watch the Two Towers in preperation for Return of the King, It was only Heather, Alsadair and Myself, but we were later joined by Becky W. and Richard. Richard showed off his snakeboarding skills :) which was amusing, and Becky tried to learn, Alasdair had a go but failed miserably and just scooted himself along the floor. 

I wonder what the weekend holds, I hope its good. 

I dreamt about you again last night.
